Cephalexin should be administered with careful monitoring in the presence of renal impairment (creatinine clearance < 30 mL/min, with or without dialysis). Under such conditions, careful clinical observation and laboratory studies renal function monitoring should be conducted because safe dosage may be lower than that usually recommended  [see Dosage and Administration (

                              2.3

                           )].Monitor patients longer for toxicity and drug interactions due to delayed clearance.
